Utterance.UttText: Natalie Karikas, 79 yrs old under Dr Ross, came in with stomach pain and jaundice.
She's got a history of diabetes and obesity.
She is feeling tired, dizzy and she is feeling depressed.
Her urine is very dark and been sent for urine MCS.
She just came into our ward 3 hrs ago.
Obs have been done and they are all stable.
She needs assistance in walking and should be referred to physio.
She is on diabetic diet and on QID BGLS.
She's charted on endone and morphine for pain.
She hasn't been seen by the team yet. and that's all I can tell you about her.
She is here for further investigation.
